Node.js is a runtime environment for executing JavaScript code outside of a web browser.
It is built on the V8 JavaScript engine, which is the same engine used by Google Chrome. 
Node.js allows developers to use JavaScript for server-side scripting, 
enabling the creation of dynamic web applications and services.

Some key features of Node.js include:
a. We can run js outside of the browser.
b. Js can talk to native machine because of c++
c. You can create web server using js


